[
  {
    "text": "We are now 2 minutes to the bomb run.",
    "start": 6.319,
    "duration": 10.01
  },
  {
    "text": "No fighters, no flack as yet.",
    "start": 11.36,
    "duration": 8.289
  },
  {
    "text": "[Music]",
    "start": 16.329,
    "duration": 3.32
  },
  {
    "text": "[Music]",
    "start": 22.65,
    "duration": 7.01
  },
  {
    "text": "UT.",
    "start": 28.32,
    "duration": 5.129
  },
  {
    "text": "[Music]",
    "start": 29.66,
    "duration": 3.789
  },
  {
    "text": "[Music]",
    "start": 36.38,
    "duration": 3.179
  },
  {
    "text": "Primary is no go. Three passes and the",
    "start": 44.64,
    "duration": 5.52
  },
  {
    "text": "aim point still obscured. Flax accurate",
    "start": 47.44,
    "duration": 6.84
  },
  {
    "text": "for altitude and getting close.",
    "start": 50.16,
    "duration": 4.12
  },
  {
    "text": "Navigator plot course southwest to",
    "start": 55.44,
    "duration": 5.0
  },
  {
    "text": "Nagasaki.",
    "start": 57.44,
    "duration": 3.0
  },
  {
    "text": "[Music]",
    "start": 63.27,
    "duration": 5.64
  },
  {
    "text": "[Applause]",
    "start": 67.69,
    "duration": 3.749
  },
  {
    "text": "[Music]",
    "start": 68.91,
    "duration": 5.889
  },
  {
    "text": "In 1942, when Nazi Germany controlled",
    "start": 71.439,
    "duration": 4.801
  },
  {
    "text": "much of Europe,",
    "start": 74.799,
    "duration": 3.201
  },
  {
    "text": ">> the United States and its allies were",
    "start": 76.24,
    "duration": 4.08
  },
  {
    "text": "working on the most secretive, ambitious",
    "start": 78.0,
    "duration": 4.64
  },
  {
    "text": "project in history, the Manhattan",
    "start": 80.32,
    "duration": 5.119
  },
  {
    "text": "Project, a race to beat the Nazis to the",
    "start": 82.64,
    "duration": 5.6
  },
  {
    "text": "first atomic bomb. The weapon was",
    "start": 85.439,
    "duration": 5.121
  },
  {
    "text": "developed at Los Alamos, high above",
    "start": 88.24,
    "duration": 4.879
  },
  {
    "text": "Santa Fe, New Mexico, where scientists",
    "start": 90.56,
    "duration": 5.36
  },
  {
    "text": "built a plutonium implosion device.",
    "start": 93.119,
    "duration": 4.721
  },
  {
    "text": "After years of roundthe-clock research",
    "start": 95.92,
    "duration": 4.32
  },
  {
    "text": "and industrial effort, they proved it",
    "start": 97.84,
    "duration": 5.56
  },
  {
    "text": "could work.",
    "start": 100.24,
    "duration": 3.16
  },
  {
    "text": "Just before dawn on July 16th, 1945, at",
    "start": 104.799,
    "duration": 6.32
  },
  {
    "text": "a remote site called Trinity in the",
    "start": 108.72,
    "duration": 5.6
  },
  {
    "text": "Hornado del Muerto Desert, the device",
    "start": 111.119,
    "duration": 5.68
  },
  {
    "text": "nicknamed the gadget detonated with a",
    "start": 114.32,
    "duration": 6.839
  },
  {
    "text": "yield of about 21 kilotons.",
    "start": 116.799,
    "duration": 4.36
  },
  {
    "text": "Night turned to day and a man-made sun",
    "start": 131.44,
    "duration": 6.439
  },
  {
    "text": "rose over the desert.",
    "start": 134.08,
    "duration": 3.799
  },
  {
    "text": "President Harry Truman was in Potdam",
    "start": 145.68,
    "duration": 4.32
  },
  {
    "text": "when news of Trinity reached him. A",
    "start": 147.76,
    "duration": 4.88
  },
  {
    "text": "coded cable from New Mexico reported the",
    "start": 150.0,
    "duration": 5.12
  },
  {
    "text": "test had been successful beyond",
    "start": 152.64,
    "duration": 4.319
  },
  {
    "text": "expectations.",
    "start": 155.12,
    "duration": 4.32
  },
  {
    "text": "It changed the tone of the conference",
    "start": 156.959,
    "duration": 4.321
  },
  {
    "text": "with Churchill and Stalin across the",
    "start": 159.44,
    "duration": 5.6
  },
  {
    "text": "table. Truman now knew the bomb worked.",
    "start": 161.28,
    "duration": 5.84
  },
  {
    "text": "On July 24th, he told Stalin",
    "start": 165.04,
    "duration": 4.32
  },
  {
    "text": "deliberately vague that the United",
    "start": 167.12,
    "duration": 3.92
  },
  {
    "text": "States had a weapon of unusual",
    "start": 169.36,
    "duration": 4.64
  },
  {
    "text": "destructive power. Stalin with a smirk",
    "start": 171.04,
    "duration": 5.36
  },
  {
    "text": "replied, \"I hope you'll make good use of",
    "start": 174.0,
    "duration": 5.04
  },
  {
    "text": "it against the Japanese.\"",
    "start": 176.4,
    "duration": 4.559
  },
  {
    "text": "knowing full well about the secrets of",
    "start": 179.04,
    "duration": 5.279
  },
  {
    "text": "the Manhattan project through espionage.",
    "start": 180.959,
    "duration": 6.721
  },
  {
    "text": "2 days later on July 26th came the",
    "start": 184.319,
    "duration": 6.321
  },
  {
    "text": "Potdam Declaration issued by the United",
    "start": 187.68,
    "duration": 6.8
  },
  {
    "text": "States, Britain and China. It called on",
    "start": 190.64,
    "duration": 6.4
  },
  {
    "text": "Japan to surrender unconditionally,",
    "start": 194.48,
    "duration": 4.88
  },
  {
    "text": "promised no enslavement of the nation,",
    "start": 197.04,
    "duration": 4.72
  },
  {
    "text": "but demanded disarmament and war crimes",
    "start": 199.36,
    "duration": 5.04
  },
  {
    "text": "trials, and warned that if Japan failed",
    "start": 201.76,
    "duration": 5.28
  },
  {
    "text": "to meet these demands, it would face",
    "start": 204.4,
    "duration": 5.759
  },
  {
    "text": "prompt and utter destruction.",
    "start": 207.04,
    "duration": 5.44
  },
  {
    "text": "In Tokyo, the divided leadership",
    "start": 210.159,
    "duration": 4.961
  },
  {
    "text": "effectively did not accept, choosing to",
    "start": 212.48,
    "duration": 4.8
  },
  {
    "text": "ignore the declaration with silence",
    "start": 215.12,
    "duration": 4.32
  },
  {
    "text": "while pursuing a lastditch hope for",
    "start": 217.28,
    "duration": 4.16
  },
  {
    "text": "Soviet mediation.",
    "start": 219.44,
    "duration": 3.92
  },
  {
    "text": "But even before that answer, the",
    "start": 221.44,
    "duration": 5.519
  },
  {
    "text": "machinery was in motion. On July 25th,",
    "start": 223.36,
    "duration": 5.76
  },
  {
    "text": "Truman approved General Carl Spart's",
    "start": 226.959,
    "duration": 4.64
  },
  {
    "text": "order authorizing the composite group to",
    "start": 229.12,
    "duration": 4.479
  },
  {
    "text": "deliver atomic bombs as soon after",
    "start": 231.599,
    "duration": 4.881
  },
  {
    "text": "August 3rd as weather permitted against",
    "start": 233.599,
    "duration": 5.28
  },
  {
    "text": "a target list that included Hiroshima,",
    "start": 236.48,
    "duration": 6.56
  },
  {
    "text": "Kakura, Nagata, and Nagasaki.",
    "start": 238.879,
    "duration": 6.481
  },
  {
    "text": "Kyoto, once at top the list, had been",
    "start": 243.04,
    "duration": 4.399
  },
  {
    "text": "removed after Secretary of War Henry",
    "start": 245.36,
    "duration": 4.56
  },
  {
    "text": "Stimson argued it was the cultural and",
    "start": 247.439,
    "duration": 5.121
  },
  {
    "text": "academic heart of Japan, and preserving",
    "start": 249.92,
    "duration": 4.48
  },
  {
    "text": "it would matter for postwar",
    "start": 252.56,
    "duration": 4.56
  },
  {
    "text": "reconciliation.",
    "start": 254.4,
    "duration": 4.799
  },
  {
    "text": "Tokyo was not chosen because months of",
    "start": 257.12,
    "duration": 4.0
  },
  {
    "text": "firebombing had already devastated the",
    "start": 259.199,
    "duration": 4.241
  },
  {
    "text": "city, making damage assessment close to",
    "start": 261.12,
    "duration": 5.519
  },
  {
    "text": "impossible. Instead, Hiroshima remained",
    "start": 263.44,
    "duration": 5.92
  },
  {
    "text": "largely untouched, making it an ideal",
    "start": 266.639,
    "duration": 5.361
  },
  {
    "text": "site to clearly gauge the atomic bomb's",
    "start": 269.36,
    "duration": 4.8
  },
  {
    "text": "devastating effects.",
    "start": 272.0,
    "duration": 5.52
  },
  {
    "text": "On August 6th, 1945, the meticulously",
    "start": 274.16,
    "duration": 4.72
  },
  {
    "text": "planned mission commenced at the",
    "start": 277.52,
    "duration": 4.48
  },
  {
    "text": "Northfield Air Base on Tinian Island. At",
    "start": 278.88,
    "duration": 6.24
  },
  {
    "text": "precisely 2:45 a.m., the silver Boeing",
    "start": 282.0,
    "duration": 6.16
  },
  {
    "text": "B29 Superfortress named Inola Gay,",
    "start": 285.12,
    "duration": 5.6
  },
  {
    "text": "piloted by Colonel Paul Tibbitz, roared",
    "start": 288.16,
    "duration": 4.8
  },
  {
    "text": "down the runway, carrying the world's",
    "start": 290.72,
    "duration": 5.52
  },
  {
    "text": "first combat ready atomic bomb, cenamed",
    "start": 292.96,
    "duration": 6.6
  },
  {
    "text": "Little Boy.",
    "start": 296.24,
    "duration": 3.32
  },
  {
    "text": "Weather's clear ahead, ceiling",
    "start": 301.199,
    "duration": 4.241
  },
  {
    "text": "unlimited.",
    "start": 303.759,
    "duration": 5.121
  },
  {
    "text": "Maintain course and altitude. ETA to the",
    "start": 305.44,
    "duration": 7.44
  },
  {
    "text": "IP on time. Two accompanying aircraft,",
    "start": 308.88,
    "duration": 6.0
  },
  {
    "text": "the Great Artiste, equipped with",
    "start": 312.88,
    "duration": 3.92
  },
  {
    "text": "instrumentation to measure the bomb's",
    "start": 314.88,
    "duration": 5.039
  },
  {
    "text": "explosive force and necessary evil,",
    "start": 316.8,
    "duration": 4.56
  },
  {
    "text": "tasked with photography and",
    "start": 319.919,
    "duration": 6.241
  },
  {
    "text": "documentation, followed closely behind.",
    "start": 321.36,
    "duration": 7.679
  },
  {
    "text": "Little Boy was a gun type uranium 235",
    "start": 326.16,
    "duration": 6.319
  },
  {
    "text": "fision bomb weighing approximately 9,700",
    "start": 329.039,
    "duration": 8.16
  },
  {
    "text": "lb or about 4,400 kg designed to achieve",
    "start": 332.479,
    "duration": 7.041
  },
  {
    "text": "critical mass through the rapid firing",
    "start": 337.199,
    "duration": 5.121
  },
  {
    "text": "of a uranium projectile into a uranium",
    "start": 339.52,
    "duration": 5.519
  },
  {
    "text": "target. This sudden union would initiate",
    "start": 342.32,
    "duration": 4.96
  },
  {
    "text": "an uncontrolled chain reaction,",
    "start": 345.039,
    "duration": 4.401
  },
  {
    "text": "releasing the equivalent explosive force",
    "start": 347.28,
    "duration": 5.6
  },
  {
    "text": "of approximately 15,000 tons or 15",
    "start": 349.44,
    "duration": 6.96
  },
  {
    "text": "kilotons of TNT.",
    "start": 352.88,
    "duration": 5.28
  },
  {
    "text": "After a 6-hour flight covering",
    "start": 356.4,
    "duration": 6.72
  },
  {
    "text": "roughly,500 m or about 2,400 km, the",
    "start": 358.16,
    "duration": 6.64
  },
  {
    "text": "formation approached the Japanese",
    "start": 363.12,
    "duration": 5.04
  },
  {
    "text": "mainland around 700 a.m. Weather",
    "start": 364.8,
    "duration": 5.92
  },
  {
    "text": "reconnaissance aircraft Straight Flush",
    "start": 368.16,
    "duration": 4.8
  },
  {
    "text": "had earlier confirmed clear skies over",
    "start": 370.72,
    "duration": 7.319
  },
  {
    "text": "Hiroshima, sealing the city's fate.",
    "start": 372.96,
    "duration": 5.079
  },
  {
    "text": "Approaching at an altitude of 31,000 ft",
    "start": 378.24,
    "duration": 6.48
  },
  {
    "text": "or about 9.5 km, Tibbitz began his",
    "start": 381.36,
    "duration": 5.76
  },
  {
    "text": "bombing run, handing final control to",
    "start": 384.72,
    "duration": 5.599
  },
  {
    "text": "Bombardier Major Thomas Faraby.",
    "start": 387.12,
    "duration": 5.44
  },
  {
    "text": "Japanese radar detected the small group",
    "start": 390.319,
    "duration": 5.521
  },
  {
    "text": "of aircraft around 7:09 a.m., prompting",
    "start": 392.56,
    "duration": 7.12
  },
  {
    "text": "initial air raid sirens in Hiroshima.",
    "start": 395.84,
    "duration": 6.079
  },
  {
    "text": "However, when observers realized it was",
    "start": 399.68,
    "duration": 4.48
  },
  {
    "text": "only three planes, the military assumed",
    "start": 401.919,
    "duration": 4.4
  },
  {
    "text": "it was merely a reconnaissance mission",
    "start": 404.16,
    "duration": 4.879
  },
  {
    "text": "rather than a bombing raid. Tragically,",
    "start": 406.319,
    "duration": 5.121
  },
  {
    "text": "they canled the alert, allowing daily",
    "start": 409.039,
    "duration": 6.081
  },
  {
    "text": "life to resume in the city.",
    "start": 411.44,
    "duration": 7.92
  },
  {
    "text": "At 8:09 a.m., the target Ioy Bridge near",
    "start": 415.12,
    "duration": 6.56
  },
  {
    "text": "the city center came clearly into view",
    "start": 419.36,
    "duration": 5.839
  },
  {
    "text": "through Faraby's Nordon bomb site.",
    "start": 421.68,
    "duration": 6.799
  },
  {
    "text": "Precisely at 8:15 a.m., as Inola Gay",
    "start": 425.199,
    "duration": 5.921
  },
  {
    "text": "reached the optimal release point, Farra",
    "start": 428.479,
    "duration": 4.641
  },
  {
    "text": "triggered the mechanism, opening the",
    "start": 431.12,
    "duration": 4.56
  },
  {
    "text": "bomb bay doors and releasing Little Boy",
    "start": 433.12,
    "duration": 5.88
  },
  {
    "text": "toward Hiroshima.",
    "start": 435.68,
    "duration": 3.32
  },
  {
    "text": "Approximately 43 seconds after release,",
    "start": 439.28,
    "duration": 4.96
  },
  {
    "text": "Little Boy reached its predetermined",
    "start": 442.4,
    "duration": 5.28
  },
  {
    "text": "detonation altitude of 600 m or just",
    "start": 444.24,
    "duration": 6.399
  },
  {
    "text": "over 650 yd above the Shimmer surgical",
    "start": 447.68,
    "duration": 5.919
  },
  {
    "text": "clinic, missing the intended target,",
    "start": 450.639,
    "duration": 7.201
  },
  {
    "text": "Ayoi Bridge, by roughly 240 m or about",
    "start": 453.599,
    "duration": 7.281
  },
  {
    "text": "260 yd.",
    "start": 457.84,
    "duration": 6.0
  },
  {
    "text": "At this precise height, radar alimters",
    "start": 460.88,
    "duration": 5.28
  },
  {
    "text": "triggered internal mechanisms that fired",
    "start": 463.84,
    "duration": 6.72
  },
  {
    "text": "the uranium projectile into the target.",
    "start": 466.16,
    "duration": 4.4
  },
  {
    "text": "initiating an instantaneous unstoppable",
    "start": 471.199,
    "duration": 6.761
  },
  {
    "text": "nuclear chain reaction.",
    "start": 474.08,
    "duration": 3.88
  },
  {
    "text": "The explosion occurred in less than a",
    "start": 484.4,
    "duration": 4.079
  },
  {
    "text": "microcond, unleashing energy equivalent",
    "start": 486.16,
    "duration": 6.56
  },
  {
    "text": "to approximately 15 kilotons of TNT.",
    "start": 488.479,
    "duration": 7.601
  },
  {
    "text": "Instantly, a brilliant blinding flash of",
    "start": 492.72,
    "duration": 6.0
  },
  {
    "text": "white light engulfed the city, visible",
    "start": 496.08,
    "duration": 5.2
  },
  {
    "text": "for miles around, momentarily brighter",
    "start": 498.72,
    "duration": 5.28
  },
  {
    "text": "than the sun.",
    "start": 501.28,
    "duration": 4.479
  },
  {
    "text": "Observers on the ground described an",
    "start": 504.0,
    "duration": 4.319
  },
  {
    "text": "intense burst followed by an enormous,",
    "start": 505.759,
    "duration": 6.561
  },
  {
    "text": "deafening boom. A fiery nuclear fireball",
    "start": 508.319,
    "duration": 7.361
  },
  {
    "text": "formed, rapidly expanding to about 200 m",
    "start": 512.32,
    "duration": 6.88
  },
  {
    "text": "or 216 yd in radius, vaporizing",
    "start": 515.68,
    "duration": 5.76
  },
  {
    "text": "everything it touched.",
    "start": 519.2,
    "duration": 4.639
  },
  {
    "text": "Radiating outward, the blast wave",
    "start": 521.44,
    "duration": 5.2
  },
  {
    "text": "produced staggering devastation. Within",
    "start": 523.839,
    "duration": 6.961
  },
  {
    "text": "roughly 340 m or 370 yd, nearly all",
    "start": 526.64,
    "duration": 5.84
  },
  {
    "text": "reinforced concrete buildings were",
    "start": 530.8,
    "duration": 4.08
  },
  {
    "text": "obliterated with fatalities approaching",
    "start": 532.48,
    "duration": 4.24
  },
  {
    "text": "100%.",
    "start": 534.88,
    "duration": 5.36
  },
  {
    "text": "outward to about 1.7 km or just over a",
    "start": 536.72,
    "duration": 6.48
  },
  {
    "text": "mile. Residential buildings collapsed.",
    "start": 540.24,
    "duration": 5.92
  },
  {
    "text": "Widespread fires ignited and massive",
    "start": 543.2,
    "duration": 6.24
  },
  {
    "text": "loss of life occurred. At even greater",
    "start": 546.16,
    "duration": 8.08
  },
  {
    "text": "distances up to 4.5 km or 2.8 mi, the",
    "start": 549.44,
    "duration": 7.2
  },
  {
    "text": "shock wave shattered windows, injuring",
    "start": 554.24,
    "duration": 4.159
  },
  {
    "text": "thousands who had curiously approached",
    "start": 556.64,
    "duration": 4.56
  },
  {
    "text": "windows after seeing the flash.",
    "start": 558.399,
    "duration": 5.12
  },
  {
    "text": "The intense thermal radiation inflicted",
    "start": 561.2,
    "duration": 4.96
  },
  {
    "text": "thirdderee burns, penetrating skin",
    "start": 563.519,
    "duration": 4.801
  },
  {
    "text": "layers deeply and rendering thousands of",
    "start": 566.16,
    "duration": 3.92
  },
  {
    "text": "survivors severely disfigured or",
    "start": 568.32,
    "duration": 3.36
  },
  {
    "text": "disabled.",
    "start": 570.08,
    "duration": 5.52
  },
  {
    "text": "Within approximately 2 km or 1.2 mi, the",
    "start": 571.68,
    "duration": 5.36
  },
  {
    "text": "heat was severe enough to cause",
    "start": 575.6,
    "duration": 4.64
  },
  {
    "text": "instantaneous thirdderee burns and fires",
    "start": 577.04,
    "duration": 5.44
  },
  {
    "text": "erupted throughout the city, creating a",
    "start": 580.24,
    "duration": 6.56
  },
  {
    "text": "deadly firestorm that raged for hours.",
    "start": 582.48,
    "duration": 7.039
  },
  {
    "text": "Of Hiroshima's roughly 350,000",
    "start": 586.8,
    "duration": 5.599
  },
  {
    "text": "inhabitants, approximately 70,000 to",
    "start": 589.519,
    "duration": 5.841
  },
  {
    "text": "80,000 people, died instantly from the",
    "start": 592.399,
    "duration": 6.241
  },
  {
    "text": "blast, heat, and immediate radiation,",
    "start": 595.36,
    "duration": 5.599
  },
  {
    "text": "many leaving only eerie human-shaped",
    "start": 598.64,
    "duration": 5.12
  },
  {
    "text": "shadows behind, permanently etched into",
    "start": 600.959,
    "duration": 5.281
  },
  {
    "text": "pavement and walls.",
    "start": 603.76,
    "duration": 4.16
  },
  {
    "text": "Thousands more perished over the",
    "start": 606.24,
    "duration": 3.599
  },
  {
    "text": "following months and years, succumbing",
    "start": 607.92,
    "duration": 4.8
  },
  {
    "text": "to radiation sickness, burns, and",
    "start": 609.839,
    "duration": 5.281
  },
  {
    "text": "associated cancers, pushing total",
    "start": 612.72,
    "duration": 5.6
  },
  {
    "text": "casualties to well over 140,000 people",
    "start": 615.12,
    "duration": 7.12
  },
  {
    "text": "by the end of 1945 alone.",
    "start": 618.32,
    "duration": 6.32
  },
  {
    "text": "Later that same day, President Truman",
    "start": 622.24,
    "duration": 4.56
  },
  {
    "text": "addressed the world solemnly declaring",
    "start": 624.64,
    "duration": 4.4
  },
  {
    "text": "that if Japan did not surrender,",
    "start": 626.8,
    "duration": 5.2
  },
  {
    "text": ">> \"If they do not now accept our terms,",
    "start": 629.04,
    "duration": 5.28
  },
  {
    "text": "they may expect a reign of ruin from the",
    "start": 632.0,
    "duration": 4.8
  },
  {
    "text": "air the like of which has never been",
    "start": 634.32,
    "duration": 4.72
  },
  {
    "text": "seen on this earth.\"",
    "start": 636.8,
    "duration": 4.64
  },
  {
    "text": ">> Despite the unprecedented destruction,",
    "start": 639.04,
    "duration": 5.12
  },
  {
    "text": "Japan's leaders, paralyzed by internal",
    "start": 641.44,
    "duration": 5.04
  },
  {
    "text": "division and disbelief, still did not",
    "start": 644.16,
    "duration": 4.96
  },
  {
    "text": "offer surrender. So the decision",
    "start": 646.48,
    "duration": 6.479
  },
  {
    "text": "followed to drop another atomic bomb.",
    "start": 649.12,
    "duration": 7.04
  },
  {
    "text": "On August 9th, 1945, 3 days after",
    "start": 652.959,
    "duration": 5.601
  },
  {
    "text": "Hiroshima was destroyed, another",
    "start": 656.16,
    "duration": 4.32
  },
  {
    "text": "meticulously planned atomic bombing",
    "start": 658.56,
    "duration": 4.16
  },
  {
    "text": "mission took off from Northfield Air",
    "start": 660.48,
    "duration": 5.039
  },
  {
    "text": "Base on Tinian Island, aiming to compel",
    "start": 662.72,
    "duration": 4.88
  },
  {
    "text": "Japan's surrender.",
    "start": 665.519,
    "duration": 4.961
  },
  {
    "text": "This time, six B29 aircraft were",
    "start": 667.6,
    "duration": 5.52
  },
  {
    "text": "assigned specific roles. The primary",
    "start": 670.48,
    "duration": 5.68
  },
  {
    "text": "aircraft, a silver B29 named Boxcar,",
    "start": 673.12,
    "duration": 5.36
  },
  {
    "text": "piloted by Major Charles Sweeney,",
    "start": 676.16,
    "duration": 5.04
  },
  {
    "text": "carried Fat Man, a plutoniumbased",
    "start": 678.48,
    "duration": 5.599
  },
  {
    "text": "implosion type atomic bomb, far more",
    "start": 681.2,
    "duration": 4.879
  },
  {
    "text": "sophisticated and powerful than the",
    "start": 684.079,
    "duration": 5.841
  },
  {
    "text": "uranium based device used on Hiroshima.",
    "start": 686.079,
    "duration": 6.0
  },
  {
    "text": "The Great Artiste was tasked again with",
    "start": 689.92,
    "duration": 4.72
  },
  {
    "text": "blast measurement instrumentation",
    "start": 692.079,
    "duration": 4.081
  },
  {
    "text": "while Big Stink was assigned",
    "start": 694.64,
    "duration": 4.639
  },
  {
    "text": "photographic documentation.",
    "start": 696.16,
    "duration": 5.76
  },
  {
    "text": "Two weather reconnaissance planes, Inola",
    "start": 699.279,
    "duration": 5.761
  },
  {
    "text": "Gay, monitoring conditions over Kokura",
    "start": 701.92,
    "duration": 6.32
  },
  {
    "text": "and Laggin Dragon checking Nagasaki flew",
    "start": 705.04,
    "duration": 5.919
  },
  {
    "text": "ahead and a spare aircraft Full House",
    "start": 708.24,
    "duration": 4.96
  },
  {
    "text": "returned early due to technical issues",
    "start": 710.959,
    "duration": 4.88
  },
  {
    "text": "and did not proceed to the target.",
    "start": 713.2,
    "duration": 5.28
  },
  {
    "text": "Shortly after takeoff, Boxgar faced a",
    "start": 715.839,
    "duration": 5.041
  },
  {
    "text": "significant problem. A fuel transfer",
    "start": 718.48,
    "duration": 5.359
  },
  {
    "text": "pump failed, leaving around 640 gall of",
    "start": 720.88,
    "duration": 6.56
  },
  {
    "text": "fuel unusable. Meanwhile, Big Stink",
    "start": 723.839,
    "duration": 5.281
  },
  {
    "text": "failed to correctly make the planned",
    "start": 727.44,
    "duration": 4.399
  },
  {
    "text": "rendevous over Yakushima Island south of",
    "start": 729.12,
    "duration": 4.959
  },
  {
    "text": "the Japanese mainland. Flying at the",
    "start": 731.839,
    "duration": 4.401
  },
  {
    "text": "wrong altitude and executing long dog",
    "start": 734.079,
    "duration": 4.401
  },
  {
    "text": "leg patterns rather than the briefed",
    "start": 736.24,
    "duration": 4.719
  },
  {
    "text": "tight circles causing confusion and",
    "start": 738.48,
    "duration": 5.359
  },
  {
    "text": "delay, the formation proceeded toward",
    "start": 740.959,
    "duration": 6.241
  },
  {
    "text": "Kokura, their primary target.",
    "start": 743.839,
    "duration": 6.0
  },
  {
    "text": "Upon arrival, visibility was critically",
    "start": 747.2,
    "duration": 5.52
  },
  {
    "text": "impaired, partially due to clouds, but",
    "start": 749.839,
    "duration": 4.641
  },
  {
    "text": "mostly because workers at the nearby",
    "start": 752.72,
    "duration": 4.48
  },
  {
    "text": "Yahhata Steel Works deliberately burned",
    "start": 754.48,
    "duration": 5.76
  },
  {
    "text": "coal tar to create thick black smoke,",
    "start": 757.2,
    "duration": 5.12
  },
  {
    "text": "intentionally obscuring the city from",
    "start": 760.24,
    "duration": 5.039
  },
  {
    "text": "bombing raids. Boxgar attempted three",
    "start": 762.32,
    "duration": 5.6
  },
  {
    "text": "separate bombing runs over Kakura, each",
    "start": 765.279,
    "duration": 4.481
  },
  {
    "text": "unsuccessful as Bombardier Captain",
    "start": 767.92,
    "duration": 4.32
  },
  {
    "text": "Kermit Bayan struggled to visually",
    "start": 769.76,
    "duration": 5.12
  },
  {
    "text": "confirm the aiming point.",
    "start": 772.24,
    "duration": 5.039
  },
  {
    "text": "Adding to their urgency, increasingly",
    "start": 774.88,
    "duration": 4.72
  },
  {
    "text": "accurate Japanese anti-aircraft fire",
    "start": 777.279,
    "duration": 5.281
  },
  {
    "text": "bracketed the aircraft. Eventually,",
    "start": 779.6,
    "duration": 5.52
  },
  {
    "text": "after the third failed pass, the crew",
    "start": 782.56,
    "duration": 4.64
  },
  {
    "text": "abandoned Kokura for their secondary",
    "start": 785.12,
    "duration": 4.159
  },
  {
    "text": "target, Nagasaki.",
    "start": 787.2,
    "duration": 4.639
  },
  {
    "text": "The failed attempt on Kokura later gave",
    "start": 789.279,
    "duration": 5.36
  },
  {
    "text": "rise to the phrase Kokura's luck,",
    "start": 791.839,
    "duration": 5.041
  },
  {
    "text": "referring to narrowly escaping disaster",
    "start": 794.639,
    "duration": 5.041
  },
  {
    "text": "without even realizing it.",
    "start": 796.88,
    "duration": 4.8
  },
  {
    "text": "As Boxgar turned southwest toward",
    "start": 799.68,
    "duration": 5.44
  },
  {
    "text": "Nagasaki, fuel became critically low.",
    "start": 801.68,
    "duration": 5.44
  },
  {
    "text": "Although the crew had agreed beforehand",
    "start": 805.12,
    "duration": 3.92
  },
  {
    "text": "that landing with a fully armed atomic",
    "start": 807.12,
    "duration": 4.399
  },
  {
    "text": "bomb was too risky, making ditching the",
    "start": 809.04,
    "duration": 5.359
  },
  {
    "text": "Fat Man at sea preferable, it was",
    "start": 811.519,
    "duration": 5.601
  },
  {
    "text": "decided that radar bombing over Nagasaki",
    "start": 814.399,
    "duration": 4.721
  },
  {
    "text": "could be performed if visual targeting",
    "start": 817.12,
    "duration": 4.399
  },
  {
    "text": "failed, with jettisoning as a last",
    "start": 819.12,
    "duration": 5.6
  },
  {
    "text": "resort only.",
    "start": 821.519,
    "duration": 6.241
  },
  {
    "text": "Shortly before 11:00 a.m., the formation",
    "start": 824.72,
    "duration": 6.16
  },
  {
    "text": "arrived over Nagasaki. Visibility here",
    "start": 827.76,
    "duration": 5.6
  },
  {
    "text": "too was poor, but a sudden break in",
    "start": 830.88,
    "duration": 5.199
  },
  {
    "text": "cloud cover allowed Behan a momentary",
    "start": 833.36,
    "duration": 6.56
  },
  {
    "text": "visual confirmation of the target.",
    "start": 836.079,
    "duration": 6.32
  },
  {
    "text": "At precisely 11:00 a.m., the Great",
    "start": 839.92,
    "duration": 4.719
  },
  {
    "text": "Artiste dropped instrument packages",
    "start": 842.399,
    "duration": 4.56
  },
  {
    "text": "designed to measure the blast.",
    "start": 844.639,
    "duration": 5.361
  },
  {
    "text": ">> Instrument canister away. Shoots good.",
    "start": 846.959,
    "duration": 6.601
  },
  {
    "text": "Signals live.",
    "start": 850.0,
    "duration": 3.56
  },
  {
    "text": "Roger. Great artisteist. Hold your",
    "start": 854.0,
    "duration": 5.199
  },
  {
    "text": "track. We're awaiting visual on target.",
    "start": 856.16,
    "duration": 6.16
  },
  {
    "text": ">> 1 minute later at 11:01 a.m. Behan",
    "start": 859.199,
    "duration": 3.601
  },
  {
    "text": "shouted,",
    "start": 862.32,
    "duration": 2.72
  },
  {
    "text": ">> \"I've got it. I've got it.\"",
    "start": 862.8,
    "duration": 6.44
  },
  {
    "text": ">> And released the Fat Man bomb.",
    "start": 865.04,
    "duration": 4.2
  },
  {
    "text": "At exactly 11:02 a.m., Fat Man detonated",
    "start": 885.76,
    "duration": 6.079
  },
  {
    "text": "above Nagasaki, unleashing another",
    "start": 889.44,
    "duration": 5.92
  },
  {
    "text": "devastating atomic blast upon Japan.",
    "start": 891.839,
    "duration": 7.601
  },
  {
    "text": "Fat Man detonated approximately 503 m or",
    "start": 895.36,
    "duration": 7.919
  },
  {
    "text": "550 yd above Nagasaki, exploding with a",
    "start": 899.44,
    "duration": 6.88
  },
  {
    "text": "yield of roughly 21 kotons.",
    "start": 903.279,
    "duration": 5.841
  },
  {
    "text": "Immediately, an immense nuclear fireball",
    "start": 906.32,
    "duration": 7.519
  },
  {
    "text": "measuring around 222 m or 243 yd in",
    "start": 909.12,
    "duration": 7.6
  },
  {
    "text": "radius engulfed the city center,",
    "start": 913.839,
    "duration": 4.721
  },
  {
    "text": "momentarily generating temperatures",
    "start": 916.72,
    "duration": 5.119
  },
  {
    "text": "hotter than the surface of the sun.",
    "start": 918.56,
    "duration": 5.2
  },
  {
    "text": "Anything within this volume was simply",
    "start": 921.839,
    "duration": 3.521
  },
  {
    "text": "obliterated.",
    "start": 923.76,
    "duration": 4.96
  },
  {
    "text": "Buildings, vehicles, and human beings",
    "start": 925.36,
    "duration": 5.2
  },
  {
    "text": "erased from existence in a blinding",
    "start": 928.72,
    "duration": 3.28
  },
  {
    "text": "flash.",
    "start": 930.56,
    "duration": 3.279
  },
  {
    "text": "The initial blast wave extended",
    "start": 932.0,
    "duration": 3.92
  },
  {
    "text": "outwards, delivering catastrophic",
    "start": 933.839,
    "duration": 4.161
  },
  {
    "text": "destruction within a radius of roughly",
    "start": 935.92,
    "duration": 6.96
  },
  {
    "text": "760 m or 830 yd where reinforced",
    "start": 938.0,
    "duration": 7.519
  },
  {
    "text": "concrete buildings were demolished.",
    "start": 942.88,
    "duration": 6.16
  },
  {
    "text": "Within a wider radius of about 1.7 km or",
    "start": 945.519,
    "duration": 6.0
  },
  {
    "text": "just above a mile, residential and",
    "start": 949.04,
    "duration": 5.44
  },
  {
    "text": "commercial buildings collapsed, fires",
    "start": 951.519,
    "duration": 5.76
  },
  {
    "text": "ignited uncontrollably, and casualties",
    "start": 954.48,
    "duration": 5.76
  },
  {
    "text": "became widespread. Tens of thousands of",
    "start": 957.279,
    "duration": 5.761
  },
  {
    "text": "Nagasaki's residents experienced severe",
    "start": 960.24,
    "duration": 6.719
  },
  {
    "text": "injuries or were trapped beneath debris.",
    "start": 963.04,
    "duration": 6.479
  },
  {
    "text": "By the end of 1945,",
    "start": 966.959,
    "duration": 5.44
  },
  {
    "text": "approximately 60,000 to 80,000 people in",
    "start": 969.519,
    "duration": 5.12
  },
  {
    "text": "Nagasaki had perished from the",
    "start": 972.399,
    "duration": 4.641
  },
  {
    "text": "explosion, fires, and immediate",
    "start": 974.639,
    "duration": 4.481
  },
  {
    "text": "radiation effects.",
    "start": 977.04,
    "duration": 4.32
  },
  {
    "text": "Adding to Japan's problems, shortly",
    "start": 979.12,
    "duration": 4.399
  },
  {
    "text": "before midnight on August 8th, the",
    "start": 981.36,
    "duration": 4.159
  },
  {
    "text": "Soviet Union launched a massive invasion",
    "start": 983.519,
    "duration": 4.961
  },
  {
    "text": "of Japanese-held Manuria, shattering",
    "start": 985.519,
    "duration": 5.361
  },
  {
    "text": "Japan's last desperate hope for Soviet",
    "start": 988.48,
    "duration": 4.96
  },
  {
    "text": "mediation. Facing the overwhelming",
    "start": 990.88,
    "duration": 4.72
  },
  {
    "text": "reality of dual catastrophes, the",
    "start": 993.44,
    "duration": 4.319
  },
  {
    "text": "unprecedented devastation from atomic",
    "start": 995.6,
    "duration": 4.32
  },
  {
    "text": "bombings, and the massive Soviet",
    "start": 997.759,
    "duration": 5.041
  },
  {
    "text": "offensive, Emperor Hirohito acknowledged",
    "start": 999.92,
    "duration": 5.76
  },
  {
    "text": "the futility of continued resistance,",
    "start": 1002.8,
    "duration": 5.12
  },
  {
    "text": "declaring to his people that the enemy",
    "start": 1005.68,
    "duration": 6.399
  },
  {
    "text": "possessed a new and most cruel bomb.",
    "start": 1007.92,
    "duration": 7.359
  },
  {
    "text": "Finally, on August 15th, 1945,",
    "start": 1012.079,
    "duration": 4.88
  },
  {
    "text": "Japan announced its unconditional",
    "start": 1015.279,
    "duration": 3.281
  },
  {
    "text": "surrender.",
    "start": 1016.959,
    "duration": 3.361
  },
  {
    "text": "The formal surrender document was signed",
    "start": 1018.56,
    "duration": 4.16
  },
  {
    "text": "aboard the battleship USS Missouri in",
    "start": 1020.32,
    "duration": 6.32
  },
  {
    "text": "Tokyo Bay on September 2nd, 1945,",
    "start": 1022.72,
    "duration": 7.119
  },
  {
    "text": "officially ending World War II.",
    "start": 1026.64,
    "duration": 5.6
  },
  {
    "text": "Today, 80 years have passed since",
    "start": 1029.839,
    "duration": 4.24
  },
  {
    "text": "humanity first unleashed atomic",
    "start": 1032.24,
    "duration": 4.719
  },
  {
    "text": "destruction upon itself. 8 decades since",
    "start": 1034.079,
    "duration": 5.76
  },
  {
    "text": "that fateful event, often called man's",
    "start": 1036.959,
    "duration": 5.681
  },
  {
    "text": "last bomb, the world still lives under",
    "start": 1039.839,
    "duration": 5.6
  },
  {
    "text": "the shadow of nuclear annihilation. The",
    "start": 1042.64,
    "duration": 5.6
  },
  {
    "text": "hope remains that Hiroshima and Nagasaki",
    "start": 1045.439,
    "duration": 6.161
  },
  {
    "text": "will forever mark the first, the last,",
    "start": 1048.24,
    "duration": 6.0
  },
  {
    "text": "and only time these weapons were ever",
    "start": 1051.6,
    "duration": 6.199
  },
  {
    "text": "used in war.",
    "start": 1054.24,
    "duration": 3.559
  }
]